messages.text: Jack arrives to find Mike boxing Hazel in against the wall.
Come on, let me give you a ride.
She doesn’t need one.
What are you doing here?
I’m her ride.
That’s my boyfriend. I told you.
Oh my god. You’re kidding.
Him?
Don’t…
Ha! No, seriously, this is a joke.
Not a joke.
It feels like it.
Nope. Not a joke.
You should have believed me.
So you were single yesterday afternoon when I drove you home.
And today, you’ve got a new boyfriend?
You move pretty fast. I like fast girls.
Mike, back off.
Throwing up his hands with his palms facing out, Mike leaves.
Thanks Jack!
He kept trying to get me into his car.
Kept saying he was trying to make up for yesterday.
Don’t worry about it.
But let’s leave before he comes back.
Or someone else shows up…
And…I think I actually need to go home after school…
What? I thought we were going to meet at the park.
I’d rather take you home so I know you’re safe.
I don’t want Mike to do something stupid like follow us.
Let’s play it cool, okay?
Okay, I guess…
After Jack drops Hazel off at home, he texts Brady when he’s back to his own house.
So? How’d it go today?
It went okay, maybe except for at the end.
I think we pulled it off, though.
What happened?
Mike still tried to make her go home with him.
I wasn’t around when it happened. But then I got there fast, after she texted me.
I’m still not feeling great about it.
Where are you now?
Home. I dropped her off first.
Man, you’re lucky. Maybe you should back off.
You’ve done enough.
I can’t just abandon her.
What do you think is going to happen?
Jack, once those guys stop messing with her…she’s going to want to go find a real boyfriend.
Yeah, and that could be me.
You don’t know her.
I saw the two of you together.
Dude. Girls like her don’t date guys like us.
She's the type of girl who dates football guys.
Don’t talk about her like she’s some sort of snob.
Don’t get mad at me for being real.
She’s out of your league.
If you’re going to be negative, I don’t want to hear it.
But someone needs to tell you that you’re going to be disappointed.
Seriously. If she wanted you, she’d have said ‘be my boyfriend’.
Not ‘be my fake boyfriend’.
She put you in friend-zone area.
You’ll never get out of it.
I’m not talking to you.
Do you want an honest opinion or a yes man?
Because you know I won’t lie to you.
But you’ll assume things about her when you don’t know her?
What a standup guy.
Ugh.
Fine.
If you want to test it out, do something sweet for her.
I’m not testing her. She’s not a lab rat.
I don’t mean it like that.
I’m just saying if you like her, show her.
Get her a small gift or something. Not enough to be a big deal.
I’d get her something, but I’m broke.
What do you even get a girl like her?
Wait…
I have an idea.
Whatever it is, good luck.
After spending a nice morning together —
Riding to school and chatting in the hallways —
Hazel texts Jack after the first bell.
Made it to class 😅
I almost didn’t make it.
The hall was crowded on my way, so I couldn’t get through.
We shouldn’t talk so much, I guess.
Worth it.
Hey, just so you know, I put something in your bag this morning.
You did?
Yeah, I want to surprise you. Hope you don’t mind.
This little packet?
What? You didn’t have to get me something.
Open it up.
OMG!
They are so…wow!
Where did you find them?
Do you like them?
Old news clippings. Old book paper. Faded journal pages…
These are so hard to find. Everyone always throws them away.
I can’t believe it 😍
I remembered last night, I had a box of old stuff from my grandparents.
There might be more, actually. I didn’t have a chance to go through all of it.
These are from your grandparents? Are you sure you don’t want them?
They don’t do any good sitting in a box.
Why not give them to someone who likes them?
Jack…
I checked with my mom too. Really.
I want you to have them.
Everyone always laughs about my junk journals.
You’re so nice to give these to me.
There’s nothing to laugh about. It’s your hobby.
Thanks 🙂
I can’t wait to use them.
You’re welcome.
So want to meet after class?
Of course!
Whenever you want to.
Want to fake hold hands? ;)
I think it helps with the whole fake boyfriend thing.
Well, I guess so.
Yeah…I mean, if you want to…
Do I make you uncomfortable?
No. I like being with you.
I like talking to you.
I thought you were having fun.
Having a fake girlfriend isn’t so bad, is it?
Not…bad…I actually like this.
I just didn’t want to admit it.
I like it, too 😊
